WEBVTT

00:55.500 --> 00:59.129
You don't like flying, do you?

00:59.237 --> 01:01.603
What gives you that idea?

01:03.708 --> 01:04.640
You want to know the secret...

01:04.742 --> 01:08.371
to surviving air travel?

01:08.479 --> 01:09.571
After you get
where you're going,

01:09.681 --> 01:11.206
take off your shoes and socks.

01:11.317 --> 01:13.080
Then walk around,

01:13.185 --> 01:15.847
making fists
with your toes.

01:15.954 --> 01:17.854
Fists with your toes?

01:19.391 --> 01:20.858
It sounds crazy,

01:20.959 --> 01:23.894
but I've been doing it
for nine years.

01:23.996 --> 01:26.931
Better than a shower
and a cup of coffee.

01:28.534 --> 01:29.558
Okay.

01:39.478 --> 01:41.208
It's okay.
I'm a cop.

01:42.882 --> 01:44.440
Trust me.

01:44.551 --> 01:47.587
I've been doing this
for 11 years.

01:47.687 --> 01:50.155
<i>On behalf of
the captain and crew,</i>

01:50.256 --> 01:53.123
<i>we'd like to welcome you
to Los Angeles.</i>

01:53.226 --> 01:55.126
<i>Have a very Merry Christmas.</i>

02:10.043 --> 02:13.912
<i>Flight 227 to Tucson
now boarding at gate 14.</i>

02:27.027 --> 02:28.085
Ah.

02:29.697 --> 02:31.597
How do you do?

02:42.544 --> 02:43.943
Ladies and gentlemen.

02:44.045 --> 02:45.945
Ladies and gentlemen!

02:46.047 --> 02:49.949
I want to congratulate
each and every one of you...

02:50.051 --> 02:52.952
for making this
one of the greatest years...

02:53.054 --> 02:55.955
in the history
of the Nakatomi Corporation.

02:57.559 --> 03:00.392
On behalf of
the chief executive officer,

03:00.495 --> 03:03.396
Mr. Ozu,
and the board of directors,

03:03.498 --> 03:05.898
we wish you
a Merry Christmas...

03:06.001 --> 03:08.060
and a Happy New Year!

03:08.171 --> 03:09.570
Merry Christmas!

03:09.672 --> 03:11.401
Happy New Year!

03:11.507 --> 03:12.906
Hey, Holly,

03:13.009 --> 03:14.408
what about
dinner tonight, huh?

03:14.510 --> 03:17.411
Harry, it's Christmas Eve.

03:17.513 --> 03:20.414
Families, stockings...

03:22.351 --> 03:23.909
chestnuts...

03:24.020 --> 03:25.419
Rudolph and Frosty.

03:25.521 --> 03:28.422
Any of these things
ring a bell?

03:28.524 --> 03:30.424
Actually, I was
thinking more...

03:30.526 --> 03:33.427
of mulled wine,
a nice aged brie,

03:33.529 --> 03:35.429
and a roaring fireplace.

03:35.531 --> 03:37.431
You know what I'm saying?

03:40.036 --> 03:41.436
Ginny, it's 5:40.

03:41.538 --> 03:44.439
Go join the party.
Have some champagne.

03:44.541 --> 03:47.442
You're making me feel
like Ebenezer Scrooge.

03:47.544 --> 03:50.445
Can the baby
handle a little sip?

03:50.547 --> 03:52.947
That baby's ready
to tend bar.

03:53.050 --> 03:55.075
Last chance.

03:55.185 --> 03:56.277
Bye.

04:02.493 --> 04:05.951
McClane residence.
Lucy McClane speaking.

04:06.064 --> 04:07.554
Hello, Lucy McClane.

04:07.665 --> 04:09.565
This is
your mother speaking.

04:09.667 --> 04:11.066
Mommy!

04:11.169 --> 04:13.069
When are you
coming home?

04:13.171 --> 04:15.071
Pretty soon.
Pretty soon.

04:15.173 --> 04:18.574
You'll be in bed
when I get there, though.

04:18.676 --> 04:20.576
Let me talk to Paulina.

04:20.678 --> 04:23.078
And no snooping
around the house,

04:23.181 --> 04:24.614
looking for presents.

04:24.716 --> 04:27.082
Is Daddy coming home
with you?

04:29.354 --> 04:31.254
Well, we'll see what...

04:31.356 --> 04:33.756
Santa and Mommy
can do, okay?

04:33.858 --> 04:35.758
Put Paulina on.
Bye, honey.

04:35.860 --> 04:37.452
Paulina!

04:42.535 --> 04:44.560
<i>Hola, Mrs. Holly.</i>

04:44.670 --> 04:47.434
Um, did Mr. McClane call?

04:47.540 --> 04:50.441
<i>No, Mrs. Holly.
No telefono.</i>

04:50.543 --> 04:52.943
Well, he probably just
didn't have time...

04:53.045 --> 04:54.444
before his flight.

04:54.547 --> 04:57.277
Um, make up
the spare bedroom...

04:57.383 --> 04:58.782
just in case.

04:58.884 --> 05:01.444
<i>Si, Mrs. Holly.
I do that already.</i>

05:01.554 --> 05:04.387
What would I do
without you, Paulina?

05:24.511 --> 05:25.910
Oh!

05:29.516 --> 05:31.211
California.

05:43.531 --> 05:45.431
Hey, I'm John McClane.

05:45.533 --> 05:47.091
Argyle.

05:47.201 --> 05:48.998
I'm your limo driver.

05:51.339 --> 05:53.364
Nice bear.

05:57.545 --> 05:59.445
Okay... Argyle.

05:59.547 --> 06:02.015
What do we do now?

06:02.116 --> 06:03.879
You tell me.

06:03.985 --> 06:06.920
It's my first time
driving a limo.

06:07.022 --> 06:10.014
This is my first time
riding in one.

06:10.158 --> 06:13.059
Relax. We got everything
in this mug, man.

06:13.161 --> 06:16.392
Look at this-
CD, CB, TV,

06:16.498 --> 06:19.058
telephone, full bar, VHS.

06:20.602 --> 06:22.900
If your friend's
hot to trot,

06:23.005 --> 06:25.405
I know a few
mama bears.

06:25.507 --> 06:27.407
Or is he married?

06:27.509 --> 06:28.908
He's married.

06:29.011 --> 06:30.410
Okay.

06:30.512 --> 06:32.412
Oh, sorry about that.

06:32.514 --> 06:34.414
It's the girl's day off.

06:34.516 --> 06:37.918
I didn't know
you were gonna sit up front.

06:38.021 --> 06:40.921
So, uh, your lady
live out here?

06:41.025 --> 06:42.924
About the past
six months.

06:43.026 --> 06:45.927
Meaning you still
live in New York?

06:46.029 --> 06:48.623
You always ask
this many questions, Argyle?

06:48.731 --> 06:50.358
Sorry, man.
I used to drive a cab.

06:50.466 --> 06:52.229
People would expect
a little chitchat.

06:52.335 --> 06:53.666
So you divorced?

06:53.770 --> 06:55.670
Just drive the car, man.

06:55.772 --> 06:58.172
Come on.
You divorced?

06:58.274 --> 07:00.606
You separated?
She beat you up?

07:02.378 --> 07:04.778
She had a good job.

07:04.881 --> 07:06.781
It turned into
a great career.

07:06.884 --> 07:09.785
<i>That meant
she had to move here.</i>

07:09.887 --> 07:12.287
You're very fast, Argyle.

07:12.389 --> 07:15.324
<i>So why didn't you come?</i>

07:17.394 --> 07:18.554
<i>Well?</i>

07:18.662 --> 07:20.186
What's up?

07:20.297 --> 07:22.629
Because I'm
a New York cop.

07:22.733 --> 07:26.134
I got a six-month backlog
of New York scumbags.

07:26.236 --> 07:29.364
I can't just pick up
and go that easy.

07:29.473 --> 07:32.465
You thought
she wouldn't make it out here,

07:32.576 --> 07:34.976
so why bother
to pack, right?

07:35.079 --> 07:37.981
Like I said,
you're very fast, Argyle.

07:38.082 --> 07:41.109
You mind if we
hear some tunes?

07:44.355 --> 07:47.722
Hey, that will work.

07:47.826 --> 07:51.091
Don't you got
any Christmas music?

