28:00.878 --> 28:02.402
Oh,

28:02.513 --> 28:05.277
that's beautiful.

28:05.383 --> 28:07.783
I always enjoyed
to make models...

28:07.885 --> 28:09.785
when I was a boy.

28:09.887 --> 28:11.286
The exactness,

28:11.389 --> 28:13.789
the attention to every
conceivable detail.

28:13.891 --> 28:17.327
It's beautiful.

28:17.428 --> 28:20.226
Is this what this is all about?
Our project in Indonesia?

28:20.331 --> 28:23.300
<i>Contrary to what
you people may think,</i>

28:23.401 --> 28:25.801
<i>we're going to
develop that region,</i>

28:25.903 --> 28:27.302
<i>not exploit it.</i>

28:27.405 --> 28:29.066
I believe you.

28:29.173 --> 28:32.302
<i>I read the article
in Forbes.</i>

28:34.179 --> 28:36.613
Mr. Takagi,

28:37.616 --> 28:41.052
I could talk about industrialization
and men's fashions all day,

28:41.153 --> 28:43.178
but I'm afraid
work must intrude,

28:43.288 --> 28:45.813
and my associate here
has some questions for you.

28:45.924 --> 28:50.418
Sort of fill-in-the-blanks
questions, actually.

28:59.939 --> 29:01.600
I don't have that code!

29:01.708 --> 29:04.438
You broke in here
to access our computer?

29:06.146 --> 29:09.638
Any information you could get, when
they wake up in Tokyo, they'll change it.

29:09.749 --> 29:12.616
<i>You won't be able to blackmail
our executives, threaten our pro-</i>

29:12.719 --> 29:14.778
Sit... down!

29:24.064 --> 29:27.329
Mr. Takagi,
I'm really not interested...

29:27.434 --> 29:28.958
in your computer.

29:33.074 --> 29:35.474
But I need the code key...

29:35.576 --> 29:39.478
<i>because I am interested
in the $640 million...</i>

29:39.580 --> 29:41.480
in negotiable bearer bonds...

29:41.582 --> 29:44.483
that you have
locked in your vault.

29:44.585 --> 29:48.749
And the computer
controls the vault.

29:48.856 --> 29:50.983
You want money?

29:51.092 --> 29:54.755
What kind
of terrorists are you?

29:57.098 --> 30:00.500
Who said
we were terrorists?

30:19.554 --> 30:23.957
<i>The bonds represent
at most ten days'...</i>

30:24.059 --> 30:26.527
<i>operating capital
for your parent organization.</i>

30:35.238 --> 30:37.365
The code, please.

30:38.007 --> 30:39.235
It's useless to you.

30:39.342 --> 30:43.301
There are seven vault safeguards,
and the code key's only one of them.

30:43.412 --> 30:45.243
You'll never get it open.

30:45.348 --> 30:48.249
Then there's no reason
not to tell us.

30:48.351 --> 30:49.545
I told you.

30:49.652 --> 30:51.745
It's not over yet.

30:56.359 --> 30:58.259
It's a very nice suit...

30:58.361 --> 31:00.353
Mr. Takagi.

31:00.464 --> 31:03.194
It would be a shame
to ruin it.

31:06.303 --> 31:08.931
I'm going to
count to three.

31:09.039 --> 31:12.008
<i>There will not be a four.</i>

31:12.109 --> 31:13.736
Give me...

31:13.844 --> 31:16.711
the code.

31:16.813 --> 31:18.212
One...

31:20.317 --> 31:22.251
<i>Two...</i>

31:24.321 --> 31:26.346
- Three.
- I don't know it. I'm telling you!

31:26.456 --> 31:28.048
Get on the jet to Tokyo
and ask the chairman.

31:28.158 --> 31:30.992
I'm telling you.
You're just gonna have to kill me.

31:31.095 --> 31:32.289
Okay.

31:35.466 --> 31:37.832
We'll do it
the hard way.

31:37.936 --> 31:39.927
Tony, see if you
can dispose of that.

31:40.038 --> 31:43.303
Karl, better check
on Heinrich's work.

32:08.167 --> 32:09.657
Nothing.

32:09.768 --> 32:11.633
See to Heinrich.

32:13.239 --> 32:14.638
Now...

32:14.740 --> 32:17.641
you can
break the code?

32:17.743 --> 32:19.643
You didn't
bring me along...

32:19.745 --> 32:21.645
for my charming
personality.

32:28.255 --> 32:31.156
Argyle, tell me
you heard the shots.

32:31.258 --> 32:32.987
You're callin'
the police right now.

32:34.594 --> 32:36.152
Of course
I'm coming by later.

32:36.263 --> 32:38.663
Have I ever lied to you?

32:38.765 --> 32:42.098
My boss?
Thinks I'm on my way to Vegas.

32:42.202 --> 32:45.660
Uli, get up on the pipes.

32:45.772 --> 32:48.673
Marco, you go
through here.

32:48.775 --> 32:51.676
I'll throw you the cord.

32:55.782 --> 32:57.978
Hans, we're on the roof.

33:11.032 --> 33:12.624
Here.

33:24.812 --> 33:27.144
Thirty minutes
to break the code,

33:27.248 --> 33:30.150
Two hours, two and a half hours
for the five mechanicals...

33:30.252 --> 33:31.651
at the minimum.

33:31.753 --> 33:35.154
The seventh lock,
however, is out of my hands.

33:57.714 --> 33:59.181
I'm sorry-

33:59.282 --> 34:01.614
The seventh lock-
the electromagnetic seal.

34:01.718 --> 34:03.083
You do understand...

34:03.186 --> 34:05.017
the circuits cannot
be cut locally.

34:06.723 --> 34:08.815
Trust me.

34:08.991 --> 34:12.188
Why the fuck
didn't you stop him,John?

34:13.795 --> 34:16.697
'Cause then
you'd be dead, too, asshole!

34:16.799 --> 34:18.699
Think, goddamn it!
Think!

34:31.315 --> 34:33.112
We've got a fire alarm.

34:33.217 --> 34:34.706
Call 911.

34:34.818 --> 34:38.719
Give them the guard's name
and the building code number,

34:38.822 --> 34:40.880
and cancel the alarm.

34:40.991 --> 34:42.719
Then disable the system.

34:44.328 --> 34:47.126
On what floor
did the alarm go off?

34:48.831 --> 34:51.232
Now, shall we go?

34:51.335 --> 34:52.734
<i>Nein.</i>

35:04.282 --> 35:06.182
Oh, baby, come to Papa.

35:06.284 --> 35:07.683
Come on.

35:13.491 --> 35:16.085
Come on, baby.
Come to Papa.

35:16.194 --> 35:18.185
<i>I'll kiss
your fuckin'dalmatian.</i>

35:21.299 --> 35:23.096
You stupid motherfuckers!
No!

35:23.201 --> 35:26.568
Turn the fuckin' truck around!

35:59.339 --> 36:03.173
The fire has been
called off, my friend.

36:06.279 --> 36:09.680
No one is coming to help you.

36:13.286 --> 36:16.915
You might as well
come out and join the others.

36:19.292 --> 36:21.692
I promise
I won't hurt you.

36:50.958 --> 36:53.222
Drop it, dickhead.
It's the police.

36:53.327 --> 36:55.227
You won't hurt me.

36:55.329 --> 36:56.729
Yeah? Why not?

36:56.832 --> 36:59.232
Because
you're a policeman.

36:59.334 --> 37:01.666
There are rules
for policemen.

37:01.770 --> 37:06.139
Yeah. That's what
my captain keeps telling me.

37:32.302 --> 37:33.701
Aah!

38:12.409 --> 38:14.969
You bet your ass
I wish to proceed.

38:55.487 --> 38:57.149
Nine million terrorists
in the world,

38:57.256 --> 39:00.487
and I got to kill one
with feet smaller than my sister.

39:49.209 --> 39:52.042
I wanted this
to be professional,

39:52.145 --> 39:54.613
efficient, and cooperative.

39:54.715 --> 39:56.843
Not a lot to ask.

39:56.951 --> 39:59.852
Alas, Mr. Takagi
did not see it that way,

39:59.954 --> 40:04.857
so he won't be joining us
for the rest of his life.

40:04.959 --> 40:07.860
<i>We can go
any way you want it.</i>

40:07.962 --> 40:10.726
<i>You can walk out
or be carried out,</i>

40:10.832 --> 40:14.996
but have no illusions-
we are in charge.

40:15.103 --> 40:20.507
<i>So... decide now, each of you,</i>

40:20.608 --> 40:22.269
<i>And please remember...</i>

40:23.945 --> 40:26.005
<i>we have left nothing
to chance.</i>

40:34.123 --> 40:35.681
Get them back!

40:44.133 --> 40:47.830
" Now I have
a machine gun.

40:49.638 --> 40:52.766
<i>Ho-ho-ho. "</i>

40:55.645 --> 40:57.545
A security guard
we missed?

40:57.647 --> 41:00.480
They're usually
just growing fat on a pension.

41:00.583 --> 41:02.983
This is
something else.

41:11.995 --> 41:14.486
We have to do
something, Hans.

41:14.597 --> 41:16.121
Yes, we do.

41:16.232 --> 41:18.757
Tell Karl his brother is dead.

41:18.868 --> 41:20.733
Tell him
to come down.

41:20.837 --> 41:23.328
<i>Karl...
komm sofort.</i>

41:23.439 --> 41:29.003
<i>Franco,you and Fritz take
the body upstairs and out of sight.</i>

41:29.113 --> 41:31.172
<i>I don't want the hostages
to think too much.</i>

42:34.013 --> 42:35.480
Aah!

42:35.581 --> 42:37.310
I want blood!

42:37.416 --> 42:40.010
But let Heinrich
plant the detonators.

42:40.119 --> 42:43.020
The police will waste hours
trying to negotiate.

42:43.122 --> 42:46.023
Then you can
tear the building apart.

42:46.125 --> 42:49.356
But until then,
do not alter the plan.

42:49.462 --> 42:51.987
And if he alters it?

42:56.136 --> 42:58.229
What do you think?

43:00.574 --> 43:02.474
Something's wrong.

43:02.576 --> 43:03.975
Cops?

43:05.579 --> 43:06.978
John.

43:07.080 --> 43:10.345
<i>John-Aw, Christ!
He can fuck this whole thing up!</i>

43:10.450 --> 43:12.441
<i>What does
he think he's doing?</i>

43:12.552 --> 43:13.849
His job.

43:13.954 --> 43:16.354
Bullshit. His job's
3,000 miles away.

43:16.456 --> 43:20.859
Without him, we might
be able to get out of here.

43:20.961 --> 43:24.363
Tell that to Takagi.

43:47.488 --> 43:50.218
Mayday. Mayday,
Anyone copying channel nine.

43:50.325 --> 43:52.725
Terrorists have seized
the Nakatomi Building...

43:52.827 --> 43:54.318
<i>and are holding
30 hostages.</i>

43:54.430 --> 43:56.523
<i>Unknown number
of terrorists-</i>

43:56.632 --> 43:59.931
Six or more armed
with automatic weapons.

44:00.035 --> 44:03.232
Where's the best place
to transmit?

44:03.339 --> 44:04.670
<i>- Somebody answer me, goddamn it!
- The roof!</i>

44:04.773 --> 44:06.240
<i>Go! Go!</i>

44:08.811 --> 44:11.245
<i>It's the same
address as that fire signal.</i>

44:11.347 --> 44:12.746
I'll handle it.

44:14.850 --> 44:16.750
Attention,
whoever you are,

44:16.852 --> 44:19.252
this channel
is reserved for emergencies.

44:19.355 --> 44:20.822
No shit, lady!

44:20.923 --> 44:22.823
I'm not ordering
a pizza!

44:34.504 --> 44:37.268
No one kills him
but me.

44:39.342 --> 44:41.276
They have
killed one hostage.

44:41.378 --> 44:43.107
They are fortifying
their positions...

44:43.213 --> 44:44.680
while you're jerking
me off on the radio!

44:44.781 --> 44:46.772
Sir, I've
already told you.

44:46.883 --> 44:48.783
This is
a reserved channel.

44:48.885 --> 44:52.286
If this is
an emergency call, dial 911.

44:52.389 --> 44:56.349
Otherwise, I'll report
this as an FCC violation.

44:56.460 --> 45:00.453
Fine! Come and arrest me,
just send the police now!

45:02.066 --> 45:03.431
Ow!

45:13.944 --> 45:18.677
See if there's a
black-and-white to do a drive-by.

45:28.860 --> 45:31.192
Thought you guys
just ate doughnuts.

45:31.296 --> 45:33.821
They're for my wife.

45:33.932 --> 45:35.866
Yeah.

45:35.967 --> 45:37.798
She's pregnant.

45:37.903 --> 45:39.427
Yeah.

45:39.538 --> 45:42.302
Bag it.

45:42.407 --> 45:44.307
Big time.

45:46.978 --> 45:48.377
Thanks.

45:51.483 --> 45:53.884
Dispatch
to 8-Lincoln-30. Over.

45:53.986 --> 45:56.386
This is 8-Lincoln-30.
Come on in. Over.

45:56.489 --> 45:57.888
Investigate a Code 2...

45:57.990 --> 45:59.890
at Nakatomi Plaza,
Century City.

45:59.992 --> 46:01.658
8- Lincoln-30 to dispatch.
I'm on my way.

46:01.693 --> 46:03.324
8- Lincoln-30 to dispatch.
I'm on my way.

48:01.918 --> 48:03.317
Girls.

48:18.935 --> 48:22.736
Shit! Where the fuck?

48:43.461 --> 48:44.860
Oh, my God.

49:00.912 --> 49:02.812
He's in the elevator shaft.

49:04.516 --> 49:06.814
Perfect.
The elevators are locked off.

49:06.918 --> 49:09.682
Just shut him in
and come back down.

49:13.425 --> 49:14.824
Oh, fuck.

49:20.799 --> 49:23.098
Karl, the police
are probably...

49:23.202 --> 49:25.067
on their way already.

49:45.958 --> 49:47.357
Christ.

49:52.633 --> 49:54.931
I can stall them but not
if they hear gunshots.

49:55.035 --> 49:57.503
If you lock him in,
he'll be neutralized-

51:01.404 --> 51:04.066
Come out to the coast!

51:04.173 --> 51:06.300
We'll get together,
have a few laughs.

51:13.349 --> 51:17.012
Now I know
what a TV dinner feels like.

51:26.396 --> 51:28.296
<i>Such!</i>

52:23.956 --> 52:26.117
<i>Karl, komm!
Die polizei!</i>

52:26.225 --> 52:27.852
<i>Die polizei!</i>

53:11.671 --> 53:14.071
Well, it's about time.

53:20.180 --> 53:22.080
No signs
of disturbance, dispatch.

53:22.182 --> 53:23.979
Possible crank call.

53:24.084 --> 53:26.075
<i>Check the area
and confirm.</i>

53:32.026 --> 53:34.824
Who's driving this car?
Stevie Wonder?

53:36.597 --> 53:38.690
I see a guard inside.

53:38.799 --> 53:41.597
<i>I'm going in
for a closer look.</i>

53:41.702 --> 53:43.101
<i>Use caution.</i>

53:46.206 --> 53:47.503
Eddie?

53:47.608 --> 53:50.100
I had a feelin'
you'd be callin'.

54:13.168 --> 54:16.194
Evenin', Officer.
What can I do for you?

54:24.680 --> 54:27.615
Heh heh heh!

54:27.717 --> 54:30.584
We had
that false alarm, you know.

54:30.686 --> 54:32.586
That computer
sent you out...

54:32.688 --> 54:34.588
on another
wild-goose chase.

54:34.690 --> 54:36.089
They been chasing bugs...

54:36.192 --> 54:38.092
since they installed
this system.

54:38.194 --> 54:40.094
<i>Notre Dame
on top of USC-</i>

54:40.196 --> 54:41.663
Ah, shit!

54:41.764 --> 54:44.324
I got 50 bucks bet
on them assholes.

54:46.002 --> 54:50.064
<i>Come on, come on.
Where's the fucking cavalry?</i>

54:56.213 --> 54:57.339
Ah!

55:11.662 --> 55:13.254
Bah!

55:13.363 --> 55:15.388
<i>...was good for 52 yards.</i>

55:15.499 --> 55:17.399
Mind if I look around?

55:17.501 --> 55:19.402
Help yourself.

55:19.504 --> 55:21.904
<i>Seven seconds left
in this period.</i>

55:22.006 --> 55:25.442
<i>Seven to nothing,
Notre Dame.</i>

55:29.047 --> 55:30.912
Freeze, Motherfucker!

55:31.015 --> 55:32.346
Don't shoot!

55:32.450 --> 55:33.781
Drop it!

55:33.885 --> 55:35.284
Okay! Don't shoot!

55:35.386 --> 55:36.410
Drop it!

55:36.521 --> 55:38.045
Ah!

55:54.039 --> 55:55.939
Ah, the hell with this!

55:57.710 --> 55:59.234
Ah!

56:02.748 --> 56:04.716
Ah!

56:04.817 --> 56:07.377
You are dog now!

56:07.486 --> 56:10.512
No more table!
Where are you going, pal?

56:10.622 --> 56:13.216
Next time
you have a chance...

56:13.325 --> 56:14.849
to kill someone,

56:14.960 --> 56:17.121
don't hesitate.

56:22.402 --> 56:24.267
Thanks for the advice.

56:24.370 --> 56:26.270
Sorry to waste your time.

56:26.372 --> 56:27.771
No problem.

56:27.874 --> 56:29.307
Merry Christmas.

56:29.409 --> 56:30.706
Merry Christmas.

56:36.249 --> 56:40.151
# Oh, the weather outside
is frightful #

56:40.253 --> 56:42.585
# Dum de dum delightful #

56:45.258 --> 56:47.021
For the love-

56:49.663 --> 56:51.528
8- Lincoln-30
to dispatch.

56:51.632 --> 56:53.031
Go ahead.

56:53.134 --> 56:55.034
That's a wild-goose chase...

56:55.136 --> 56:56.535
here at Nakatomi Plaza.

56:56.637 --> 56:58.537
Everything here's okay.
Over.

56:58.639 --> 57:02.131
# But nobody has no place to go #

57:02.243 --> 57:05.906
# Let it snow, let it snow ##

57:07.815 --> 57:09.442
Goddamn it!
Jesus H. Christ!

57:17.224 --> 57:19.318
Welcome
to the party, pal!

57:19.427 --> 57:21.122
Goddamn it!

57:24.599 --> 57:25.998
<i># Turn up the heat #</i>

57:26.101 --> 57:27.659
<i># It's getting ready
to pop ##</i>

57:27.769 --> 57:32.365
Police under automatic
rifle fire at Nakatomi!

57:32.474 --> 57:34.465
I need back-up assistance now!

57:34.576 --> 57:37.067
Now, Goddamn it! Now!

57:55.665 --> 57:58.361
Monica,
I can get us a table.

57:58.467 --> 58:01.300
Wolfgang and I
are very close friends.

58:01.404 --> 58:03.804
I interviewed him,
for God's sake.

58:03.906 --> 58:05.305
<i>...Nakatomi.</i>

58:05.408 --> 58:07.308
<i>Repeat.
Officer needs assistance at-</i>

58:07.410 --> 58:11.813
<i>I'm at Nakatomi Plaza. They're
turning my car into Swiss cheese!</i>

58:11.914 --> 58:13.814
<i>I need
back-up assistance now!</i>

58:13.916 --> 58:15.975
<i>Now, Goddamn it! Now!</i>

58:35.939 --> 58:38.999
Never thought I'd love
to hear that sound.

58:39.109 --> 58:41.077
All of you relax.

58:41.178 --> 58:44.079
This is a matter
of inconvenient timing.

58:44.181 --> 58:46.081
Police action was inevitable...

58:46.183 --> 58:48.584
and, as it happens,
necessary.

58:48.686 --> 58:51.587
Let them fumble about outside,
and stay calm.

58:51.689 --> 58:53.350
This is simply the beginning.

58:54.659 --> 58:58.925
I thought I told all of you
I want radio silence.

58:59.030 --> 59:01.624
I didn't get
that message, Hans.

59:01.733 --> 59:05.100
You should have put it
on the bulletin board.

59:05.203 --> 59:08.502
Since I waxed Tony and Marco
and his friend,

59:08.606 --> 59:12.736
I figured you and Karl
and Franco might be lonely.

59:12.844 --> 59:15.506
How does he know
so much-

59:15.613 --> 59:18.981
That's very kind of you.

59:19.084 --> 59:21.985
I assume you are
our mysterious party crasher.

59:22.087 --> 59:26.285
You are most troublesome
for a security guard.

59:26.392 --> 59:29.190
Eeeh! Sorry, Hans.
Wrong guess.

59:29.295 --> 59:31.957
Want to go
for DoubleJeopardy,

59:32.064 --> 59:34.532
where the scores
can really change?

59:36.635 --> 59:39.468
Mm, these are
very bad for you.

59:39.571 --> 59:41.937
Who are you, then?

59:42.041 --> 59:44.532
The fly in
the ointment, Hans.

59:44.643 --> 59:46.543
The monkey
in the wrench,

59:46.645 --> 59:48.546
the pain in the ass.

59:50.016 --> 59:51.540
Whoa!

59:52.953 --> 59:55.387
Don't use the radio.

59:55.488 --> 59:59.549
See if he's lying about Marco.
Find out who's missing.

01:00:03.296 --> 01:00:05.321
Mr. Mystery Guest,

01:00:05.432 --> 01:00:07.832
are you still there?

01:00:07.934 --> 01:00:09.834
Yeah, I'm still here,

01:00:09.936 --> 01:00:13.838
unless you want to open
the front door for me.

01:00:13.940 --> 01:00:15.407
I'm afraid not,

01:00:15.508 --> 01:00:17.409
but you have me
at a loss.

01:00:17.511 --> 01:00:20.105
You know my name,
but who are you?

01:00:20.214 --> 01:00:22.045
Just another American...

01:00:22.149 --> 01:00:24.845
who saw too many movies
as a child?

01:00:24.952 --> 01:00:27.386
Another orphan
of a bankrupt culture...

01:00:27.488 --> 01:00:30.787
who thinks he's
John Wayne, Rambo,

01:00:30.891 --> 01:00:32.358
Marshal Dillon?

01:00:32.460 --> 01:00:35.361
I was always partial
to Roy Rogers, actually.

01:00:35.463 --> 01:00:37.454
I liked those
sequined shirts.

01:00:37.565 --> 01:00:40.625
Do you think you have
a chance, Mr. Cowboy?

01:00:43.170 --> 01:00:46.162
Yippee-kai-yay,
motherfucker.

01:00:49.845 --> 01:00:52.211
